The paper proposes a novel algorithmic framework for haplotype assembly from high-throughput sequencing data. The approach involves constructing a graph and using community detection to recover the haplotypes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the arXiv sub-categories of computer science that deal with graph algorithms, machine learning, computational biology, and data mining. Specifically, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DB (Databases) are all relevant sub-categories.
